🧰 - Mongoose vs MongoDB (the one you asked about)
MongoDB = database
Mongoose = tool to work with MongoDB in Node.js
- Why do we even need of mangoose

📄 - Session vs Token (JWT)

📡 - WebSockets vs HTTP
HTTP: One-way (client asks, server responds)
WebSockets: Two-way, persistent connection (like chat apps)

🔐 6. Authentication vs Authorization
Authentication: Who are you? (login)
Authorization: What are you allowed to do?
